The original work by Kaku Li provides the Python engine package
(originally `mck_ppt/`, renamed to `mbb_ppt/` in this derivative work),
including the layout methods, file-integrity / anti-corruption logic,
BLOCK_ARC chart implementations, the QA module, and the gate-script
architecture pattern. The five-stage workflow and self-refinement
protocol concepts are also adapted from Kaku Li's separate skill,
"harness-skill-upgrader" (https://github.com/likaku/harness-skill-upgrader),
also licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Modifications introduced by this derivative work include:

  - English-language documentation (CJK guidance removed).
  - Heading typography changed from Georgia (transitional serif) to
    DM Sans (modern neutral sans-serif), with Calibri fallback.
  - Body typography unified on Arial.
  - Module renamed from `mck_ppt` to `mbb_ppt`; class renamed from
    `MckEngine` to `MbbEngine`. Public-facing alias is `ExecEngine`.
    Apache 2.0 file-header copyrights from Kaku Li are preserved
    verbatim in every Python source file.
  - Primary color palette changed from McKinsey-style navy to a
    sober forest-green system; accent palette retuned to muted
    earth tones suitable for non-consulting audiences.
  - Production guard rails 11-18 added to the original 1-10 set.
  - Layout capacity matrix (`references/layout-matrix.yaml`) extended
    with explicit char_budget and tuple_arity for the S3 content gate.
  - Gate scripts translated to English and made self-locating
    relative to the skill root (no hardcoded install path).
  - Tencent Hunyuan cover-image integration (`cover_image.py`) and
    its associated Chinese prompt strings have been removed entirely.
  - CLI entry point added (`python -m mbb_ppt`) for one-shot render +
    gate execution from non-technical operator workflows.

